  15 Mar 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.38.2-r1.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug #501330

*glib-2.38.2-r1 (14 Mar 2014)

  14 Mar 2014; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  +glib-2.38.2-r1.ebuild, +files/glib-2.38.2-sigaction.patch:
  Fix uninitialized memory access in signal handler code that caused consolekit
  to fail (thanks to everybody from bug #501330 for diagnosing the issue, and
  to George L. Emigh for finding the patch).

  09 Mar 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.38.2.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug 499954

  09 Mar 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.38.2.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug 499954

  04 Mar 2014; Naohiro Aota <naota@gentoo.org>
  +files/glib-2.38.2-configure.patch, glib-2.38.2.ebuild:
  Apply a upstream patch to fix non POSIX test construction. #500996

  22 Feb 2014; Akinori Hattori <hattya@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  ia64 stable wrt bug #494132

  18 Jan 2014; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild,
  glib-2.38.2.ebuild:
  Add arm64 love.

  18 Jan 2014; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.3-r1.ebuild,
  glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  Mark m68k/s390/sh stable.

  23 Dec 2013; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Restore metadata.xml upstream tag.

*glib-2.38.2 (23 Dec 2013)

  23 Dec 2013; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org> +glib-2.38.2.ebuild,
  files/glib-2.12.12-fbsd.patch,
  files/glib-2.34.0-testsuite-skip-thread4.patch,
  files/glib-2.36.4-znodelete.patch,
  +files/glib-2.37.x-external-gdbus-codegen.patch, metadata.xml:
  Version bump for Gnome 3.10. Refresh patches with git headers.

  22 Dec 2013; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for HPPA (bug #478252).

  08 Dec 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug #478252

  30 Nov 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug #478252

  14 Nov 2013; Matt Turner <mattst88@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.3-r1.ebuild:
  alpha stable, bug 476364.

  24 Oct 2013; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.3-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for HPPA (bug #476364).

  22 Oct 2013; Christoph Junghans <ottxor@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  fixed build on Darwin (bug #488500)

  17 Oct 2013; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.3-r1.ebuild:
  arm stable, bug #476364

  13 Oct 2013; Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  Explicitly call einstalldocs in multilib_src_install_all() to accomodate bug
  #483304.

  29 Sep 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  Support compilation in clang until upstream solves this, upstream bug #691608
  (#478338 by Yuta SATOH)

  29 Sep 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> -glib-2.36.4.ebuild,
  glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild:
  Add support for win32 threads model (#472218 by Bertrand Jacquin), drop old.

  05 Sep 2013; Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.3-r1.ebuild,
  glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild, glib-2.36.4.ebuild:
  Clean up PYTHON_COMPAT from old implementations.

*glib-2.36.4-r1 (02 Sep 2013)

  02 Sep 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> -glib-2.34.3.ebuild,
  -glib-2.36.3-r1.ebuild, -glib-2.36.3-r2.ebuild, +glib-2.36.4-r1.ebuild,
  -files/glib-2.36.3-revert-ext34.patch, +files/glib-2.36.4-znodelete.patch:
  Fix segfaults in vlc and other applications that try to unload libgobject at
  runtime (bug #405173, thanks to Cédric D. for finding a good solution). Drop
  old ebuilds.

  01 Sep 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.4.ebuild:
  Pass --disable-compile-warnings configure option to drop -Werror usage

  16 Aug 2013; Lars Wendler <polynomial-c@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.3-r1.ebuild:
  Non-maintainer commit: really use python-r1 eclass.

*glib-2.36.4 (16 Aug 2013)

  16 Aug 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> -glib-2.36.3.ebuild,
  +glib-2.36.4.ebuild:
  Version bump, remove old. Includes the ext4 patch from 2.36.3-r2.

*glib-2.34.3-r1 (15 Aug 2013)

  15 Aug 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  +glib-2.34.3-r1.ebuild,
  +files/glib-2.34.3-testsuite-skip-gdbus-auth-tests.patch:
  Update ebuild for python-r1.eclass in preparation for stabilization. Skip
  another failing test (fixed in 2.36).

  15 Aug 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  glib-2.36.3-r2.ebuild:
  Restore the pkg.m4 hack from 2.34.x to prevent stage3 build failure (bug
  #481056, thanks to Markos Chandras).

  14 Aug 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild, glib-2.34.3.ebuild, glib-2.36.3.ebuild,
  glib-2.36.3-r1.ebuild, glib-2.36.3-r2.ebuild:
  Add missing libselinux dependency when USE=selinux. Disable selinux GIO
  support for non-native multilib builds until libselinux gets a multilib
  version (bug #480946, thanks to Alphat-PC).

  11 Aug 2013; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild,
  glib-2.34.3.ebuild, glib-2.36.3.ebuild, glib-2.36.3-r1.ebuild,
  glib-2.36.3-r2.ebuild:
  freebsd-lib provides its own libelf now, adjust the deps, bug #479494 by Yuta
  SATOH

  10 Aug 2013; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.3-r2.ebuild:
  Add blockers on emul-libs so that it is stacked for baselibs r10

*glib-2.36.3-r2 (10 Aug 2013)

  10 Aug 2013; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org> +glib-2.36.3-r2.ebuild:
  migrate to multilib, bug #479282

*glib-2.36.3-r1 (26 Jul 2013)

  26 Jul 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  +files/glib-2.36.3-revert-ext34.patch, +glib-2.36.3-r1.ebuild,
  -glib-2.36.2.ebuild:
  Apply upstream patch reverting a change that could cause problems with some
  ext3/4 setups, adapt bash-completion dir relying on eclass. Drop old.

  17 Jul 2013; Samuli Suominen <ssuominen@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.3.ebuild:
  Stop applying glib-2.32.4-bashcomp.patch because the upstream default of
  /usr/share/bash-completion/completions is correct as is wrt #477064

  11 Jun 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.3.ebuild:
  Add gobject-introspection blocker to ensure people don't mix different g-i and
  glib major versions as discussed with Nirbheek.

  10 Jun 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.3.ebuild:
  Stop showing warnings about dbus-glib rebuilding as looks to not be needed for
  a long time.

*glib-2.36.3 (10 Jun 2013)

  10 Jun 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +glib-2.36.3.ebuild,
  -glib-2.36.1.ebuild:
  Version bump, drop old

  05 Jun 2013; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Add upstream CPE tag (security info) from ChromiumOS.

*glib-2.36.2 (14 May 2013)

  14 May 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +glib-2.36.2.ebuild,
  -glib-2.36.0.ebuild:
  Version bump, drop old

  30 Apr 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  glib-1.2.10-r5.ebuild, glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild, glib-2.34.3.ebuild,
  +files/glib-1.2.10-automake-1.13.patch,
  +files/glib-2.34.3-automake-1.13.patch:
  On second thought, fix automake-1.13 compatibility properly, with patches.

  29 Apr 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  glib-1.2.10-r5.ebuild, glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild, glib-2.34.3.ebuild:
  Require automake-1.12, since building with 1.13 fails (bug #467086, thanks to
  Paramonov Valeriy et al.)

*glib-2.36.1 (23 Apr 2013)

  23 Apr 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +glib-2.36.1.ebuild,
  -files/glib-2.10.3-ia64-atomic-ops.patch,
  -files/glib-2.18.1-workaround-gio-test-failure-without-userpriv.patch,
  -files/glib-2.30.1-external-gdbus-codegen.patch,
  -files/glib-2.30.1-homedir-env.patch, -files/glib-2.30.2-machine-id.patch,
  -files/glib-2.30.2-missing-decls.patch,
  -files/glib-2.30.3-assert-test-failure.patch,
  -files/glib-2.30.3-closure-64bit-be.patch, -glib-2.30.3.ebuild,
  -glib-2.34.2.ebuild:
  Version bump, drop old

  07 Apr 2013; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org> glib-2.36.0.ebuild:
  Switch to python-r1, bug #458788. Do not install gtester-report man page with
  USE=-utils, bug #439344.

*glib-2.36.0 (28 Mar 2013)

  28 Mar 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  +files/glib-2.35.x-external-gdbus-codegen.patch, +glib-2.36.0.ebuild:
  Version bump for Gnome 3.8

  19 Feb 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> glib-2.30.3.ebuild,
  glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild, glib-2.34.2.ebuild, glib-2.34.3.ebuild:
  Add epatch_user (bug #453560).

  17 Feb 2013; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.3.ebuild:
  Fix xml catalog from prefix, and add ~arm-linux keyword.

  13 Jan 2013; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org> -glib-2.32.4.ebuild:
  Clean up old revision.

*glib-2.34.3 (27 Nov 2012)

  27 Nov 2012; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> -glib-2.34.1.ebuild,
  +glib-2.34.3.ebuild:
  Version bump with some minor fixes. Drop old.

*glib-2.34.2 (10 Nov 2012)

  10 Nov 2012; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> -glib-2.34.0.ebuild,
  +glib-2.34.2.ebuild:
  Version bump with various bugfixes. Drop old.

  23 Oct 2012; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  Disable problematic thread4 test, like was already done in glib-2.34.x
  ebuilds (bug #434248, thanks to Toralf Förster and Priit Laes).

*glib-2.34.1 (17 Oct 2012)

  17 Oct 2012; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.0.ebuild,
  +glib-2.34.1.ebuild:
  Version bump; fix --enable-modular-tests logic.

  14 Oct 2012; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  ia64/m68k/s390/sh/sparc stable wrt #436028

  14 Oct 2012; Matt Turner <mattst88@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha, bug 436028.

  10 Oct 2012; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  glib-2.30.3.ebuild, glib-2.32.4.ebuild, glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild,
  glib-2.34.0.ebuild:
  Drop useless USE=doc, it only regenerated documentation.

  06 Oct 2012; Anthony G. Basile <blueness@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  stable ppc ppc64, bug #427544

  06 Oct 2012; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  arm stable, bug #427544

  04 Oct 2012; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #427544

  03 Oct 2012; Pawel Hajdan jr <phajdan.jr@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  x86 stable wrt bug #427544

  02 Oct 2012; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for HPPA (bug #427544).

*glib-2.32.4-r1 (29 Sep 2012)

  29 Sep 2012; Samuli Suominen <ssuominen@gentoo.org> +glib-2.32.4-r1.ebuild,
  +files/glib-2.32.4-CVE-2012-3524.patch:
  Revision bump to import upstream patch for CVE-2012-3524 wrt #436028

  28 Sep 2012; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org> glib-2.34.0.ebuild:
  Really disable building tests when USE=-test (bug #436508, thanks to Jeff
  Kowalczyk).

  26 Sep 2012; Matt Turner <mattst88@gentoo.org> glib-2.32.4.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha, bug 427544.

